Satellite Imagery

October 19, 2022 2022-11-01 9:19

Satellite Imagery

The Easiest Way To Access Satellite Imagery

The easiest way to get information about any location on Earth is through satellite imagery. The easiest way to access it is through Olbgis Platform.

GET STARTED

Your One-Stop Shop For Satellite Imagery

Multiple Providers

Get instant access to one of the largest networks of satellite imagery providers in the world. You have higher chance of getting images that meet your needs when you use Olbgis Platform.

Competitive Prices

We've partnered with data providers to lower their minimum area requirements and offer satellite data at competitive prices. You’ll pay only for the images that you use.

Easy To Use

Olbgis Platform is so easy to use that you can purchase an image within minutes. Search our Archive for historical data or task a satellite to capture new images of your area of interest.

Customer Service

We pride ourselves on working with companies of all sizes. Our experienced team goes above and beyond to understand your geospatial needs and help you achieve your goals.

Easy To Buy

You won’t need to worry about lengthy sales processes, minimum volume commitments, and data license agreements. Just log in, search for your images, and buy what you need.

Powerful API

Send and retrieve all the information you need with one POST and one GET. Olbgis' powerful algorithms will deliver your images pre-clipped, orthorectified, and normalized.

How To Use Olbgis Platform

1. Select Your Location

Select your area of interest by drawing a polygon on the map or uploading a KML or GeoJSON file. You can also search for specific locations or coordinates.

2. Choose Your Output

Satellite sensors can capture data that is not visible on images. Choose outputs such as true color, NDVI, and near-infrared. Olbgis Platform will do the processing for you.

3. Create a Pipeline

When Olbgis Platform returns a result for your pipeline, you'll receive images that can be downloaded in GeoTIFF or PNG. We’ll never charge you if we can’t find an image.

4. Receive Your Images

When Olbgis Platform returns a result for your pipeline, you'll receive images that can be downloaded in GeoTIFF or PNG. We’ll never charge you if we can’t find an image

Collect Images Programmatically With Our API

Our powerful Olbgis API allows you to send and retrieve information with one POST and one GET. Your data will be delivered normalized, pre-clipped, and orthorectified by our powerful algorithms. If you need help while you’re building your application, you can always refer to our API documentation, which we keep up-to-date with code samples to enhance your developer experience.

Learn More

A Platform For All Your Needs

Low Res

You’ll get access to low-resolution images for free to allow you to test our platform without any risks.

Medium Res

Upgrade your plan to have access to medium-resolution images (1.6m - 8m). Pay only for the data you use.

High Res

Capture more detail with high-resolution images (50cm - 1.5m), compatible with multiple bands.

Very High Res

Get Very High Resolution (VHR) images (30cm - 80cm) in RGB, NIR, Red-Edge, and Deep Blue bands.
